BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ahrc-design-generators-round-two-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260929
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260930
SUMMARY:Deadline: AHRC: Design Generators Round Two (2026)
DESCRIPTION:Design Generators round two funds design-led research projects 
 combining design interventions with arts and humanities methodologies to c
 ontribute to the green transition. Eligible activity includes design resea
 rch prototyping\, circular business model exploration\, strengthening thir
 d-sector resilience\, skills development\, policy and strategy work\, and 
 public engagement programmes\, so exhibition-style and public-facing outpu
 ts are in scope where they sit inside a research project. Awards are GBP 1
 50\,000 to 200\,000 at 100 percent full economic cost with AHRC paying 80 
 percent\, meaning the host organisation carries a 20 percent institutional
  contribution. The lead must be a postdoctoral-standing researcher at an A
 HRC-eligible UK research organisation\, and every project must pair that l
 ead with at least one non-academic co-lead from business\, the public sect
 or\, the third sector or a community organisation\, which is the practical
  entry point for an arts organisation. Freelancers and independent consult
 ants cannot lead. The opportunity opened 21 July 2026 and closes 29 Septem
 ber 2026 at 4:00pm UK time. Decision lag is roughly three months from the 
 deadline. IMPORTANT: this round explicitly excludes international stakehol
 ders and international activity\, so non-UK partners cannot be involved.\n
 \nOrganisation: Arts and Humanities Research Council (AHRC)\, UK Research 
 and Innovation\nLocation: United Kingdom. Lead applicant must be employed 
 by\, or hold a formal written arrangement with\, a UK research organisatio
 n eligible for AHRC funding. Project activities must take place in the UK.
 \nAward: GBP 150\,000 to 200\,000 per project at 100 percent full economic
  cost\; AHRC funds 80 percent and the host research organisation must cove
 r the remaining 20 percent. Total fund GBP 1\,000\,000\, approximately 5 a
 wards. Covers research staff time\, design prototyping\, partner costs and
  public engagement activity. Subcontractors and PhD studentships are not f
 undable. No application fee.\nDuration: 9 to 12 months\, with projects req
 uired to start by 1 February 2027.\n\nMore: https://www.ukri.org/opportuni
 ty/design-generators-round-two/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_
 medium=referral
URL:https://www.ukri.org/opportunity/design-generators-round-two/?utm_sourc
 e=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:United Kingdom. Lead applicant must be employed by\, or hold a for
 mal written arrangement with\, a UK research organisation eligible for AHR
 C funding. Project activities must take place in the UK.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:tada-residency-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260812
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260813
SUMMARY:Deadline: TaDA Textile and Design Alliance: Artist in Residence Pro
 gramme 2027 (Switzerland)
DESCRIPTION:TaDA (Textile and Design Alliance) invites artists\, designers\
 , architects\, writers\, performers and interdisciplinary practitioners to
  a three-month residency in Arbon\, Eastern Switzerland\, developing new w
 ork through direct collaboration with regional textile companies and resea
 rch institutions. Applicants do not need to identify as textile artists\; 
 the programme welcomes practitioners from multiple disciplines who want to
  work with textile technology\, materials and know-how. Six residents are 
 selected annually by jury for one of two 2027 periods (April-June or Septe
 mber-November). Residents develop a new project in cooperation with local 
 textile companies\, present their work publicly and organise workshops. SU
 PPORT: accommodation\, travel expenses\, contribution to living costs\, wo
 rkspace at the Kreativzentrum ZIK\, and access to the expertise and infras
 tructure of 13 partner companies. Applicants should identify specific TaDA
  partners whose expertise contributes directly to the proposal. Apply via 
 the online form. DEADLINE: 12 August 2026\, 23:59 CEST\; selection results
  announced early November 2026.\n\nOrganisation: TaDA Textile and Design A
 lliance\nLocation: Arbon\, Eastern Switzerland (Lake Constance). Open to S
 wiss and international practitioners.\nAward: Funded residency: accommodat
 ion in Arbon a few minutes' walk from the workplace and the Bodensee\, tra
 vel expenses\, and a contribution to living costs\, plus workspace at the 
 Kreativzentrum ZIK (a former textile factory) and technology\, knowledge a
 nd infrastructure support from 13 partner textile companies and research i
 nstitutions. No application fee.\nDuration: Three months: April to June 20
 27 or September to November 2027\n\nMore: https://tada-residency.ch/en/res
 idence?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://tada-residency.ch/en/residence?utm_source=artificialnouveaugran
 tdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Arbon\, Eastern Switzerland (Lake Constance). Open to Swiss and in
 ternational practitioners.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:queer-art-design-grant-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260814
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260815
SUMMARY:Deadline: Queer|Art Design Grant 2026 (Inaugural)
DESCRIPTION:The Queer|Art Design Grant is a new initiative from Queer|Art s
 upporting projects that explore queer histories\, legacies\, and futures w
 hile providing visibility and opportunity for emerging LGBTQ+ design talen
 t. AWARDS: two USD 10\,000 grants to emerging queer creatives across the d
 esign industry\, described as the largest cash grant for LGBTQ+ designers 
 in the country. ELIGIBILITY: US-based designers working across a variety o
 f disciplines\, including graphic design\, architecture and landscape arch
 itecture\, industrial and product design\, fashion\, textile and wearables
 \, digital design\, service design\, furniture and home decor\, materials 
 research\, interior design\, and more. In its inaugural year the grant is 
 judged by a panel of designers\, curators\, architects\, and cultural lead
 ers\, including Bex McCharen\, Salome Asega\, Cristina Grajales\, Jaffer K
 olb\, and Paul Soulellis. The program is the first major initiative under 
 a new partnership between UGG and Queer|Art\; Queer|Art board member and c
 reative strategist Fran Tirado serves as Community Curator. Winners will b
 e announced at Queer|Art's Annual Party in Fall 2026. DEADLINE: 14 August 
 2026. Apply via https://www.queer-art.org/design-grant.\n\nOrganisation: Q
 ueer|Art (in partnership with UGG)\nLocation: United States\; open to US-b
 ased emerging queer/LGBTQ+ designers.\nAward: Two USD 10\,000 grants (desc
 ribed as the largest cash grant for LGBTQ+ designers in the US). No applic
 ation fee.\nDuration: One-off grant\; winners announced at Queer|Art's Ann
 ual Party\, Fall 2026\n\nMore: https://www.queer-art.org/design-grant?utm_
 source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.queer-art.org/design-grant?utm_source=artificialnouveaugran
 tdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:United States\; open to US-based emerging queer/LGBTQ+ designers.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:circolo-del-design-earthrise-26-residency-2026@artificialnouveau.github
 .io
DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260703
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260704
SUMMARY:Deadline: Circolo del Design: Earthrise 26 Residency for Young Desi
 gners 2026 (Turin)
DESCRIPTION:Earthrise 26 (Design for a Living Planet)\, the annual cultural
  initiative by Circolo del Design\, will unfold around clay and earthenwar
 e\, approached not as functional objects but as narrative\, spatial and sp
 eculative matter. One of the projects featured in the exhibition will be d
 eveloped through the Earthrise 26 Residency (5 October to 3 December 2026)
 \, a unique opportunity for an under-35 international designer to create a
 nd experiment within an interdisciplinary context. Under the mentorship of
  Designregio Kortrijk and BASE Milano among others\, the selected resident
  will collaborate with local designers\, artisans and interdisciplinary ex
 perts in Turin to produce an original body of work exhibited as part of th
 e Earthrise 26 exhibition. ELIGIBILITY: under 35\; a demonstrated internat
 ional practice through research\, collaborations\, cultural exchange or mo
 bility within Europe\; well-structured project planning with clear goals\;
  thematic relevance aligned with the objectives of Earthrise 2026\; and an
  experimental and/or innovative approach. WHAT IS OFFERED: a designer's fe
 e of EUR 1\,500 (VAT included)\, travel and accommodation for both phases\
 , a public transport pass\, up to EUR 3\,000 (VAT included) for project pr
 oduction\, a dedicated 30 sqm workspace\, and mentorship and technical/log
 istical/organisational support. Organised by Circolo del Design (circolode
 ldesign.it\; contact programma@circolodeldesign.it). Deadline: 3 July 2026
 \; results announced 20 July 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Circolo del Design\nLo
 cation: Turin\, Italy\; in-person residency.\nAward: Designer's fee of EUR
  1\,500 (VAT included)\; travel and accommodation covered for both phases 
 of the residency\; a public transport pass\; up to EUR 3\,000 (VAT include
 d) for project production\; a dedicated 30 sqm workspace within Circolo de
 l Design\; plus networking\, mentorship from interdisciplinary experts\, a
 nd technical\, logistical and organisational support. No application fee.\
 nDuration: Residency 5 October to 3 December 2026\n\nMore: https://on-the-
 move.org/news/circolo-del-design-earthrise-26-residency-young-designers-it
 aly?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://on-the-move.org/news/circolo-del-design-earthrise-26-residency-
 young-designers-italy?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=ref
 erral
LOCATION:Turin\, Italy\; in-person residency.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:van-alen-open-access-exhibition-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T130538Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260628
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260629
SUMMARY:Deadline: Van Alen Institute: Open Access - Open Call for Exhibitio
 n Proposals 2026
DESCRIPTION:Open Access: Exploring 130 Years of American Design is a reques
 t for exhibition proposals that treats the Van Alen Institute archive (tho
 usands of competition boards\, jury records\, photographs and corresponden
 ce) as living material to be questioned and reinterpreted through the lens
  of open and fair access. Van Alen invites emerging designers and creative
 s of all disciplines to engage the archive\, either responding directly to
  specific materials (competition prompts\, submitted drawings) or thematic
 ally. A wide range of media is welcomed\, including architectural models\,
  drawings\, images\, projections\, video\, photography and writing\; direc
 t engagement\, interaction and multi-disciplinary collaboration are encour
 aged. Five projects will be selected and shown together at Van Alen Instit
 ute\, 28 September to 13 November 2026. ELIGIBILITY: open to emerging crea
 tives across disciplines (architects\, artists\, designers\, filmmakers\, 
 photographers\, researchers\, writers and others)\; no formal architectura
 l training required. Applicants must be at least 18\; be legally authorize
 d to work in the United States OR capable of receiving an artist honorariu
 m (so non-US applicants able to receive an honorarium may apply\, though t
 he Brooklyn exhibition and hybrid check-ins make it US-practical)\; be ava
 ilable for hybrid check-ins July to November 2026\; and commit to deliveri
 ng exhibition-ready work on the project timeline. Collaborative proposals 
 are permitted\, though the honorarium may be shared among collaborators. S
 elected participants receive a USD 3\,000 honorarium\, archival access and
  curatorial support\, mentorship from Van Alen staff and advisors\, free m
 aterials through Materials for the Arts\, and professional documentation. 
 Supported by the National Endowment for the Arts and the New York State Co
 uncil on the Arts. Application deadline: 28 June 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Va
 n Alen Institute\nLocation: Brooklyn\, New York\, USA. Exhibition at Van A
 len Institute\, 28 September to 13 November 2026\nAward: USD 3\,000 honora
 rium\, plus archival access\, curatorial support\, mentorship\, free mater
 ials via Materials for the Arts\, professional documentation\, and inclusi
 on in the public exhibition. Five projects selected. No application fee.\n
 Duration: Hybrid project check-ins July to November 2026\; exhibition 28 S
 eptember to 13 November 2026\n\nMore: https://www.vanalen.org/project/open
 -access/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.vanalen.org/project/open-access/?utm_source=artificialnouve
 augrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Brooklyn\, New York\, USA. Exhibition at Van Alen Institute\, 28 S
 eptember to 13 November 2026
END:VEVENT
